  "texts": [
    "The kather_texture_2016_image_ tiles dataset shows that the Color-CADx model achieves high sensitivity rates for various categories, including TUMOUR, STROMA, COMPLEX, LYMPHO, DEBRIS, MUCOSA, ADIPOSE, and EMPTY (BACKGROUND).",
    "Specifically, the sensitivity rates are 97.4%, 94.9%, 93.9%, 95.7%, 97.0%, 98.4%, 97.3%, and 99.7% respectively.",
    "However, as depicted in Fig. 9, the Area Under the Curve (AUC) for both datasets is either 1 or very close to 1.",
    "This study aims to assess the effectiveness of using ensemble CNNs and transfer to automatically detect colorectal cancer WSIs.",
    "Besides, it seeks to investigate the capacity of DCT as a feature reduction and fusion algorithm."
